- namespace name="defs" defs.plim
---!
    class CLS:
        pass

doctype html
html lang="en"
    head
        - call title="Crank - Effortless macOS automation, no manual required" domain="lowtechguys.com" description="Set scripts, apps, and Shortcuts to run automatically triggered by system events." favicon="/crank/favicon.ico" icon="crank-icon" icon_size="1280" screenshot="crank-screenshot" color="rgb(255, 251, 235)" canonical="/crank/" defs:head

    body.bg-orange-linen.text-center.max-w-[100vw].flex.flex-col.items-center.min-h-[100vh].justify-between.overflow-x-hidden
        header.flex.items-center.justify-between.px-4.md:px-8.max-w-[100vw].w-[100vw].h-24.text-gray-500.justify-self-end
            a.flex.flex-center.hover:transform.hover:scale-110 href="/"
                icon.w-16.h-16.md:w-20.md:h-20.filter.drop-shadow-lg.text-gray-700 : lowtech
            .links
                a.text-sm.md:text-base.ml-4.hidden.md:inline href="/" Other apps
                a.text-sm.md:text-base.ml-4 href="/crank/presskit" Press Kit
                a.text-sm.md:text-base.ml-4 href="/crank/privacy" Privacy
                a.text-sm.md:text-base.ml-4 href="/contact?app=Crank" Contact

        section#hero.min-w-[100vw].flex-center.flex-col.relative.pb-2
            img#app-icon.w-28.h-28.md:w-32.md:h-32 src="/static/img/crank-icon.png"
            h1.mt-10.text-4xl.text-orange-bark.mb-2.drop-shadow-xl Crank
            h5.text-gray-800 Effortless macOS automation
            h5.text-gray-800.m-0.p-0.-mt-1 no manual required

            .flex.flex-center.gap-4.mt-8
                a.btn.text-black.bg-orange-200.hover:text-black.hover:bg-orange-300.rounded-lg.flex.justify-center.items-center.border-orange-stone.border-2 href="https://files.lowtechguys.com/releases/Crank.dmg"
                    icon.h-4.w-4.md:h-7.md:w-7 : package
                    span.ml-2.text-sm.md:text-base Download
                a.btn.text-black.bg-orange-200.hover:text-black.hover:bg-orange-300.rounded-lg.flex.justify-center.items-center.border-orange-stone.border-2 href="https://crank.subsol.one" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
                    icon.h-4.w-4.md:h-7.md:w-7 : credit-card
                    span.ml-2.text-sm.md:text-base Buy license
            .text-amber-950.text-xxs.mt-1.font-medium.opacity-50.mb-4
                | compatible with macOS `b 14.0+` (Sonoma and later)

            .zstack.md:w-full.max-w-[1200px]
                img#crank-hero-img.w-11/12.transition-opacity.duration-1000 src="/static/img/crank-ui.png" alt="The Crank app interface showing automation rules"
                video#crank-hero-video.shadow-none.rounded-3xl.w-full.opacity-0.transition-opacity.duration-1000 ( src="/static/video/crank.mp4" width=812 height=540 disablePictureInPicture muted loop playsinline )


        section#more.flex-center.flex-col.pb-20.space-y-24
            .flex.md:space-x-10.w-screen.max-w-[576px].md:w-auto.md:max-w-[1200px].flex-col.md:flex-row.space-y-10.md:space-y-0.px-4
                .flex.flex-col.space-y-2.md:w-1/2.text-left
                    h1.text-3xl.text-left.lg:text-4xl.mb-1.text-gray-800 When this happens, do that
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | The concept is simple: `b.text-rose-500 add a trigger` (`em when I connect my headphones`), `b.text-blue-500 set an action` (`em switch audio output`), and as if by magic, it just happens.
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | Actions can receive data about the event, like the headphones name, the screenshot file that was just taken, the calendar event that starts in 5 minutes, the battery level etc.
                    h4.text-mauve-gray Templatable fields
                    .text-sm.lg:text-base.text-gray-500
                        | All text fields like the URL from `b Open URL`, the path in `b Open File` or the `b notification title`, can use the same event data.

                .flex.flex-col.space-y-2.md:w-1/2.text-left
                    h1.text-3xl.text-left.lg:text-4xl.mb-1.text-gray-800 Write actions in plain English
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | With support for `b.text-blue-700 Gemini` and `b.text-orange-700 ChatGPT`, actions can be generated by describing the operation using natural language.
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | The AI model will receive special context about utility binaries available on your system, so that it uses commands that work on your machine.
                    h4.text-mauve-gray Private by default
                    .text-sm.lg:text-base.text-gray-500
                        | AI features are disabled by default and only run when you press the `b Generate Code` button. The context sent to the model does not contain any sensitive data.

        section#features.flex-center.flex-col.pb-20.space-y-24
            .flex.md:space-x-10.w-screen.max-w-[576px].md:w-auto.md:max-w-[1200px].flex-col.md:flex-row.space-y-10.md:space-y-0.px-4
                .flex.flex-col.space-y-2.md:w-1/2.text-left
                    h1.text-3xl.text-left.lg:text-4xl.mb-1.text-gray-800 Time window scheduling
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | Limit a rule to a `b.text-amber-700 time window` and specific `b.text-amber-700 days of the week`.
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | For example, a rule that connects to a VPN when launching the work Slack can be set to only fire on weekday mornings.
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | This can also be used to schedule actions to run daily at specific hours.

                .flex.flex-col.space-y-2.md:w-1/2.text-left
                    h1.text-3xl.md:text-left.lg:text-4xl.mb-1.text-gray-800 Rate limiting
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | Set a `b.text-amber-700 cooldown period` on a rule to avoid triggering it multiple times in a short window.
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | File system events or ambient light changes can come in bursts. Without a limit, one blip could run your action ten times before it finishes.


        section#advanced.flex-center.flex-col.pb-20.space-y-24
            .flex.md:space-x-10.w-screen.max-w-[576px].md:w-auto.md:max-w-[1200px].flex-col.md:flex-row.space-y-10.md:space-y-0.px-4
                .flex.flex-col.space-y-2.md:w-1/2.text-left
                    h1.text-3xl.text-left.lg:text-4xl.mb-1.text-gray-800 Event log
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | Every trigger event is recorded and logged along with all its data.
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | Good for figuring out what your Mac is reacting to, or `em why a rule did or didn't fire`.

                .flex.flex-col.space-y-2.md:w-1/2.text-left
                    h1.text-3xl.text-left.lg:text-4xl.mb-1.text-gray-800 Action history
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | Script output, exit codes, errors and the event that triggered the action are `em saved for each run`.
                    .text-base.lg:text-lg.text-gray-600
                        | If something triggered but didn't behave as expected, this is where to look.

        section#footer-text.flex-center.flex-col.pb-20.space-y-24
            .flex.md:space-x-10.w-screen.max-w-[576px].md:w-auto.md:max-w-[1200px].flex-col.md:flex-row.space-y-10.md:space-y-0.px-4
                .flex.flex-col.space-y-2.md:w-full.text-left
                    -md
                        ## Triggers

                        Crank listens for system events across the following categories:

                        - **Bluetooth** — device connected, device disconnected, Bluetooth on/off
                        - **Wi-Fi** — network joined, network left, Wi-Fi on/off
                        - **USB** — device connected, device disconnected
                        - **Power** — battery level, charging, screen lock/unlock, sleep/wake
                        - **Displays** — monitor connected, monitor disconnected, display count changed
                        - **Application** — app launched, quit, focused, defocused, not responding
                        - **App Windows** — window opened, closed, focused, or defocused (with title, bounds, app info)
                        - **Time** — a specific time of day reached
                        - **Calendar** — event upcoming, event started
                        - **File Watcher** — file created, changed, or deleted in a watched directory
                        - **Download** — any file downloaded, or a file matching a name pattern
                        - **Screenshot** — screenshot taken
                        - **Clipboard** — item added to clipboard, specific content type detected
                        - **Process** — any process launched or quit, filtered by name
                        - **Notifications** — notification received from any app *(macOS 15+)*
                        - **Messages** — iMessage/SMS received or sent
                        - **Mail** — email received in Apple Mail
                        - **Privacy** — camera, microphone, screen recording, or location in use
                        - **LAN** — ethernet cable connected or disconnected
                        - **Focus Mode** — a Focus mode turned on or off
                        - **Lid** *(MacBook only)* — lid opened or closed
                        - **Ambient Light** *(MacBook only)* — light level crossed a threshold
                        - **Lid Angle** *(MacBook only)* — lid angle crossed a threshold
                        - **Resource Usage** — CPU, GPU, RAM, thermal state, swap, or disk usage crossed a threshold
                        - **Spotlight** — files being tagged in Finder, files matching a type, or files larger than a specific size
                        - **Audio** — output/input device changed or connected
                        - **Visual Change** — content change or idle detected in a [Pipiri](https://lowtechguys.com/pipiri) PiP window
                        - **User Activity** — user has been idle for a certain time, or active for too long
                        - **Webhook** — receive messages from [ntfy.sh](https://ntfy.sh) topics via persistent streaming connection
                        - **Volume** — external drive or disk image mounted/unmounted
                        - **Periodic** — fire on a cron schedule (standard 5-field expressions)
                        - **Boot** — run once after system boot (within the first 5 minutes)
                        - **Script** — a custom script that can trigger on zero exit code

                        ---

                        ## Actions

                        Each rule runs one action when it fires:

                        - **Shell Script** — run any zsh script, with event details available as environment variables
                        - **AppleScript** — execute an AppleScript snippet
                        - **Shortcuts** — run a macOS Shortcut by name
                        - **Notification** — post a system notification with a custom title and body
                        - **Launch App** — open an application
                        - **Open URL** — open a URL in the default browser or a specific app
                        - **Open File** — open a file, optionally with a specific app

                        ---

                        ## Use cases

                        - Turn off notifications when a call starts
                        - Clear quarantine flag on a downloaded file
                        - Connect to a VPN when joining a specific Wi-Fi network
                        - Reposition windows when connecting a monitor
                        - Enable HDR when watching a movie, disable it when getting back to work
                        - Move downloaded invoice PDFs to an accounting folder
                        - Switch audio output when connecting Bluetooth headphones
                        - Disconnect Bluetooth devices before closing the MacBook lid
                        - Turn off True Tone and Night Shift when editing photos or videos

                        ---
                        ## Rule sharing

                        Each rule has a **Share** button that generates a unique URL you can share with others.

                        *The URL encodes the rule's trigger, conditions, and action, so that anyone can import it with one click.*

                        Below are some pre-made rules to get you started. Make sure Crank is running and just click each rule link to import it.

                        ### <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-apple-finder"></i> Apps & Windows

                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-arrow-expand"></i> [Maximize newly launched apps](https://crank.lowtechguys.com/rule/YnZ4bs0AAAC5AAAA4AN7IjIwIjoiZGVib3VuY2UiLCIyAA_lYXBwTGEAEMASaGVkiBQxMOZXaGVuIGEAA-RwcCBsGB3gBnMsIG1heGltaXplIGl0cyB3aW5kb3cAMkAwdkAIMYAJNDfgCHJheWNhc3Q6XC9cL2V4dGVuc2lvbnNcLyAYmDdcL-otbWFuYWdlbWVuABMoVwBEQEMz529wZW5VUkwIjCCe52lmZWN5Y2wIIeoxMSI6ImFueSJ9BgAAAAAAAABidngk) *(needs [Raycast](https://www.raycast.com/))*
                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-alert-02"></i> [Get notified when an app is Not Responding and click the notification to restart it](https://crank.lowtechguys.-VDbGljawCrmQBpc_iY_nRv8yDIaD8u8hkQQD9zIPo4G-RzZW5kCJHqIiRidW5kbGVJRDgc5Wdyb3VwCSXgBC5sb3d0ZWNoZ3V5cy5DcmFuay5uObHyKDHmZXhlY3V0ENI5NPGJ6Fwi7jAiOiJkZWJvdW5jZSJ9BgAAAAAAAABidngk) *(needs terminal-notifier)*
                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-git-branch"></i> [When git branch is `hotfix/` enter a focused workspace mode](https://crank.lowtechguys.com/rule/YnZ4bssDAACHAgAA4B97IjQzIjoiIyFcL2JpblwvenNoXG5cbiMgR2V0IHRoZSBicmFuY2ggbmFtZSBvZhAT4AByZXBvIGF0ICRmaWxlUGF0ADLpZ2l0ZGlyPSQoAAYQK5geXCL05CIpXG4YRwAhACrIICAtQxg0gFBcIu12LXBhcnNlIC0tYWJiCA_gB3JlZiBIRUFEIDI-XC9kZXZcL251bGwpGJvlVHJhY2sQiupsYXN0IGtub3duKKhAmnTkdm9pZABV4AAtcnVubmluZyBvbiBub24tICLnY2hhbmdlcyiT4ABfY2FjaGU9XCJcL3RtcFwvAJYgKuQtd2F0ABvoci0kKGVjaG84s_PgAXwgc2VkICdzfFwvfF98ZycpAEBIjm5YPF8IUAAS6GlmIFtbIC1mCDw4b_IAQsjDXV07ANHIySAgIPEoO-UkKGNhdDgy-AD9mQFmaepPbmx5IGFjdCBpGZEYKQgS5XVhbGx5IONogGQwSwB3iA8hPThv8TiL9yjsMB9ojD76OCr8YEJcOHb47D09IGhvdGZpeFwvKjhv9QgB7iMgRW50ZXIgYSBmb2N1CVrud29ya3NwYWNlIG1vZGUgb8g0bHNl-ED6VABT7CB3YXMgZG9uZSwgZwK0UhxiQfJv5HJtYWwYMAk45mZpIiwidgLrQAgxRjIKn-hNb2RpZmllZAATgBQ2MOtcL1VzZXJzXC9hbAsN51Byb2plY3QAEORteS1wGA3CBlwvLgAxiEYxMBi5OLf4QOF3SuwgGQTJAiBpc_MIa0Y2SEMwIIdaaVcIEggTgcdlcUincwiU6GRlYm91bmNlCB4Lq-RpbmRlCEYIDO1zaGVsbFNjcmlwdCJ9BgAAAAAAAABidngk) *(needs editing, just a starting point)*

                        ### <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-modern-tv"></i> Displays & Video

                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-computer"></i> [Disable MacBook screen when a monitor is connected](https://crank.lowtechguys.com/rule/YnZ4bvEAAADFAAAA7nsiMTEiOiJhbnkiLCIyAArgAG1vbml0b3JDb25uZWN0ZWQIF0AYMOhkZWJvdW5jZQAQiCkxMOVXaGVuICAumC8gY-ZzLCBkaXMgDekgYnVpbHQtaW4IFMhicGxhCGwgDkAPc0Yz63NoZWxsU2NyaXB0CCEIE0ASRAAMTjTgC1wvQXBwbGljYXRpb25zXC9MdW5hci5hcHBcLwCk5HRlbnQAFeVNYWNPUyAcmIQgQPvsaW4iLCJ2IjoiMSJ9BgAAAAAAAABidngk) *(needs [Lunar](https://lunar.fyi/))*
                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-tv-02"></i> [When TV is connected, position it above the MacBook display in the center](https://crank.lowtechguys.-QiIF07CPEgQQgB6mN1cmwgLWZzU0wAJeAMaHR0cHM6XC9cL2dpdGh1Yi5jb21cL2FsaW4yMzjc8uQvcmF3CBAI8hD3IJrIayAtb_U4Y_HnaG1vZCAreDgb9ZgIZmnINmVjaPhI333gAlZFUlRJQ0FMX0xBWU9VVD0kKDlK9-YgVmVydGkBLVoZTedMYXlvdXQpAD6YPyIk-YHDXCIJwutzaGVsbFNjcmlwdAoo6DMiOiJUViJ9BgAAAAAAAABidngk)
                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-video-02"></i> [Switch to "HDR Video" reference preset when focusing Final Cut Pro](https://crank.lowtechguys.com/rule/YnZ4bpQCAADgAQAA4AV7IjMiOiJzaGVsbFNjcmlwdCIsIjIAEuphcHBGb2N1c2VkABFIJDHoRmluYWwgQ3UIIkZ2SBkxSCww4BdTd2l0Y2ggdG8gSERSIGNvbG9yIHByb2ZpbGUgd2hlbiB1c2luZyA4QfJIUjTgKk1BQ19VVElMU19ESVI9XCIkSE9NRVwvLmxvY2FsXC9iaW5cL21hYy11dGlsc1wiXG5ta2RpciAtcCAALDg98wgd61xuZG93bmxvYWRfADVOX-coKSB7XG4gAAEQUwCiiGhvbEgwMTgXAGloUj35iC4vJCgp6WlmIFsgISAteAh7CJnmIiBdOyB0AN0YIAgB6mN1cmwgLWZzU0wAJeAMaHR0cHM6XC9cL2dpdGh1Yi5jb21cL2FsaW4yMzjW8uQvcmF3CBAI7BDxIHfIayAtb_U4Y_HnaG1vZCAreDgb9ZgIZmnINmVjaPhJFX3tUkVGX1BSRVNFVD0kKDki9-ABIFJlZmVyZW5jZVByZXNldCkIM-cjIEFwcGx5CN8R0udWaWRlbyByKCqQKyBwyCIgb27xCLzoIGRpc3BsYXkAPphyIiT0mB5cIphHXCL07ihQMy1TVCAyMDg0KVwiCkQabutMaWZlY3ljbGUifQYAAAAAAAAAYnZ4JA)
                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-eye"></i> [20/20/20 rule: after 20 minutes of work, display goes black to give you 20 seconds of pause](https://crank.lowtechguys._nKCkge1xuIAABEFPlIHRvb2wIaEgwMTgXAGloUj35iC4vJCgp6WlmIFsgISAteAh7CJnpIiBdOyB0aGVuGCAIAepjdXJsIC1mc1NMACXgDGh0dHBzOlwvXC9naXRodWIuY29tXC9hbGluMjM41vLkL3JhdwgQCOwQ8SB3yGsgLW_1OGPx52htb2QgK3g4G_WYCGZpyDZlY2j4SRV970lTX0NBTUVSQV9PTj0kKDkk9-AAIElzQ2FtZXJhT24pXG5pZghAODTyCIto63H06GV4aXQgMFxuCHXmXG5MVU5BCbztXC9BcHBsaWNhdGlvbgDX4AJMdW5hci5hcHBcL0NvbnRlbnQAFeVNYWNPUyAcCKEAaxBAAGTgGUAgYmxhY2tvdXQgLS1uby1taXJyb3IgYWxsIGVuYWJsZVxuc2xlZXAgAnE4OPAN6WRpc2FibGUifQYAAAAAAAAAYnZ4JA) *(needs [Lunar](https://lunar.fyi/))*

                        ### <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-folder-02"></i> Files & Storage

                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-invoice-02"></i> [Move downloaded invoices to Documents/Invoices/](https://crank.lowtechguys.)
                        - <i class="hgi-stroke hgi-shield-02"></i> [Remove quarantine flag on downloaded files](https://crank.lowtechguys.com/rule/YnZ4bqUAAACRAAAA4CV7IjEwMiI6IkNsZWFyIHF1YXJhbnRpbmUgZmxhZyBmb3IgZG93bmxvYWRlZCBmaWxlcyIsIggxCAxoG0TxABVGM-tzaGVsbFNjcmlwdAASRjEoPgAPSCI04AN4YXR0ciAtZCBjb20uYXBwbGUuOHXxyFhcIiTgAFBhdGhcIiIsInYiOiIxIn0GAAAAAAAAAGJ2eCQ)
